Gift to Kim Jong Il from Mongolian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by Mongolian President Nambariin Enkhbayar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, by D. Tsogtbaatar, advisor for Foreign Policy to the President of Mongolia on a visit to the DPRK on Wednesday.

Important Days of DPRK Celebrated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Meetings, film shows, Korean book and photo exhibitions and art performances were held in the Czech Republic, Laos, Pakistan, Russia and Indonesia from April 6 to 23 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun, the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and the 75th anniversary of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were photos showing the revolutionary feats of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, their works and books, photos and handiworks showing the achievements made by the Korean people in socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association, addressing a meeting, said that Kim Il Sung always lives in the hearts of progressive humankind for his distinguished feats performed for the country, the people and humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the Laos-Korea Tin Company said that Kim Il Sung is the great leader who devoted his all to the friendship, cooperation and solidarity among the world progressive people and a close friend of the Lao people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the film shows watched Korean films including "The Great Life in 1994", "For Liberation of the Country", "The Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks" and "Mass Gymnastic and Artistic Performance 'Arirang', 'Kim Il Sung Prize' Laureate".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary of the Russian Union of Writers said that the film offered him an opportunity to realize once again that no one on earth can match the Korean people rallied close as one around Kim Jong Il recognized by the world. He is leading the socialist cause of Korea to victory despite any pressure of the imperialists, the secretary said, adding that the DPRK is a powerful country which the U.S. styling itself the "only super power" of the world dares not provoke. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages to Kim Jong Il were adopted at meetings in the Czech Republic and Pakistan.

More Cases of GIs' Massacres of Civilians Disclosed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- More cases of massacres of civilians committed by the U.S. forces have recently been disclosed, according to the April 26th issue of the south Korean Internet newspaper Chammallo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Committee for Settling the Past History for Truth and Reconciliation found out 215 more cases of U.S. forces' massacres of civilians including killings of them through bombing in the course of classifying and confirming materials on those crimes during the Korean war according to types of crimes and regions where they were perpetrated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These cases of atrocities were as big as those of killings committed by the U.S. forces in Rogun-ri, said the newspaper. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee called for conducting a probe into the above-said cases across south Korea as early as possible.

Abolition of "Alliance" for War and Withdrawal of U.S. Forces Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration of south Korea reportedly made public a statement on April 26 at which it demanded the abolition of the south Korea-U.S. "alliance" and the withdrawal of the U.S. forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea demanded south Korea's increased share of the funds for the upkeep of the U.S. forces at a hearing of the Armed Services Committee of the U.S. Senate, the statement denounced it as an arrogant attitude of the occupation force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has so far pressurized the south Korean authorities to cover the expenses for the upkeep of the U.S. forces without paying even a single dollar for the purpose, the statement held, stressing that there is no reason for south Korea to bear the expenses for the relocation of the U.S. forces with the money collected from the people as taxes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded the "government" dissolve the "alliance" for war with the U.S. immediately and opt for peace on the Korean Peninsula through national cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the U.S. not to demand the funds for the upkeep of its forces while menacing the south Korean people but withdraw them from south Korea at once.

Art Performances Given on May Day 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Performances of national art troupes were given at parks and recreation grounds here on May 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A performance was given by artistes of the Phibada Opera Troupe at the plaza of the Arch of Triumph. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It began with choruses "Song of General Kim Jong Il" and "Song of May Day". Put on the stage were colorful numbers including female duet and chorus of famous masterpiece "Song of Sea of Blood", female solo "Girl on Steed" and male solo "May of Victory".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The artistes of the State National Art Troupe gave a performance before the Ulmil Pavilion on Moran Hill. They put on the stage kayagum ensemble "Let's Sing of Our Pride in Being under the Guidance of the General", female solo "Single-Minded Determination" and "The Country Will Know You", small chorus "Pyongyang Is Best" and dances "Janggu Dance" and "Yangsando".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Acrobats of the Pyongyang Circus presented colorful acrobatic numbers at the park of the Mangyongdae Fun Fair, delighting spectators.

Workers in North and South of Korea Meet to Mark May Day  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Changwon, May 1 (KCNA Correspondent) -- A May Day reunification meeting of workers in the north and the south of Korea for implementing the June 15 joint declaration was held in Changwon City, South Kyongsang Province, south Korea from April 29 to May 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their program included colorful functions including a meeting of workers in the north and the south for unity, a joint football match and a get-together. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The May Day unity meeting of workers in the north and the south for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration took place at the Changwon sports complex on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were delegates of the north side led by Won Hyong Guk, vice-chairman of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, delegates of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions led by Chairman Ri Sok Haeng, delegates of the Federation of south Korean Trade Unions led by Chairman Ri Yong Duk, members of the industrial and regional organizations in South Kyongsang Province and Changwon and persons of different strata in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Chung Bok, vice-chairman of the North Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration, O Jong Ryol, co-representative of the South Side Committee, and other figures of the south side were present there as guests of honor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting began with hoisting a Korean Peninsula flag. Ri Chung Bok and O Jong Ryol made congratulatory speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers stressed the need to unite in the drive for reunification irrespective of idea, political view, system and religious belief, frustrate any move of outside forces threatening existence and settle all the issues related to the destiny of the fellow countrymen by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon the workers in the north and the south to cherish their mission for the times and devote sincere efforts and patriotic enthusiasm to the peace of the country, the great unity of the nation and national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Won Hyong Guk, Ri Yong Duk and Ri Sok Haeng in their speeches underscored the need to resolutely reject the domination and interference of outside forces aimed to block the grand march for reunification of the Korean nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification, holding high the banner of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration of workers in the north and the south was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration called upon the labor movement organizations in the north and the south to hold fast to the June 15 joint declaration as a landmark of independent reunification and a beacon of hope and implement it to the letter and take the lead in implementing the tasks for giving importance to the nation, defending peace and realizing unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was followed by the joint football match of workers in the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The get-together of representatives of workers in the north and the south was held as part of the reunification meeting.

S. Korean Warmongers' Moves to Develop War Hardware under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- These days the south Korean authorities are getting frantic in their moves to reinforce and develop ultra-modern war hardware with the U.S. zealous backing and at its instigation behind the curtain of the dialogue. This is a very dangerous criminal act of blocking the process of peacefully settling the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula, escalating the military tension and driving the situation to the phase of confrontation and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson today observes this in its signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is more serious is that the south Korean warlike forces' moves for arms buildup are timed to coincide with their war exercises targeted against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The war and peace can never go together. South Korea's reckless arms buildup strongly backed by the U.S. is a criminal act of aggravating the situation on the Korean Peninsula and driving the inter-Korean relations to a crisis again. It is quite unjustifiable as it is disturbing peace and security on the peninsula and the rest of Asia, sparking off an arms race and increasing the danger of war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK will never remain a passive onlooker to the U.S. and south Korean warlike forces' reckless war moves against it behind the curtain of the dialogue but take measures to resolutely counter them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities would be well advised to clearly understand the gravity of the situation and the consequences to be entailed by it and discontinue their provocative and reckless arms buildup at once.

Rodong Sinmun on WPK's Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea is a noble patriotic politics that helps defend the sovereignty and the dignity of the nation with arms of justice and guarantees the independent reunification of the country, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the Songun politics is politics of national independence that defends the dignity and the sovereignty of the nation, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK's Songun politics guarantees the exercise of the nation's sovereign rights in accomplishing the cause of Korea's reunification with the military strength. It rejects outsiders' involvement and interference in this cause and helps the nation solve the reunification problem in accordance with its own will and interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The politics helps the Koreans in the north and the south and abroad have heightened awareness of national independence and pride and dynamically advance along the road of reunification and patriotism. It provides a sure guarantee for solving the problem of Korea's reunification for the establishment of the national sovereignty in it as a whole on the principle of national independence by the Koreans themselves. Herein lies one of reasons why the WPK's Songun politics becomes a patriotic one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This politics is also a politics for peace that helps prevent a danger of war on the Korean Peninsula and reliably protect the security of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a treasured sword of peace as it helps contain the U.S. imperialists' ever-more undisguised moves for a new war with deterrent for self-defence and create atmosphere favorable for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The invincible revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu, protect not only the DPRK from the imperialists' aggression but defend south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unshakable stand and consistent policy of the WPK to embrace all Koreans loving the country and the nation and get them united irrespective of ideology, system, class and strata to achieve the reunification of the country, the cherished desire of the nation. The Songun politics is one of great national unity as it rallies all the Koreans closer under the banner of patriotism and national reunification.

May Day Marked in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- The working people of the country significantly marked May Day, an international holiday, on May 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sports and amusement games took place at the Yanggakdo Football Stadium with the attendance of tens of thousands of people from more than 40 units under the Pyongyang City Construction Guidance Bureau. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants showed well the might of unity of constructors in such events as mass rhythmic gymnastics, Taekwon-Do for health, football, basketball, volleyball, 400-metre relay, tug-of-war and Korean wrestling. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people in the city of Hamhung held colorful functions in different parts of the city including the Hamhung Stadium and the Hungnam District Stadium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through sports and amusement games, the working people of the Hungnam Fertilizer Complex, the Hamhung Basic Foodstuff Factory, the Hamhung Knitting Factory, the Hamhung Cement Factory and other industrial establishments successfully represented the true picture of the DPRK society in which all the people help and lead each other forward. Those of the Hungnam Fertilizer Complex staged a performance of 5,000-people chorus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Workers at different units in North Hamgyong Province, including the Songjin Steel Complex, the Musan Mining Complex and the Ranam Coal Mining Machine Complex conducted various sports and amusement games including ball games, running with ankles tied and running with a toy balloon on the head. 
 On the same day, similar sports games and performances of art groups were held at industrial establishments and co-op farms in North Hwanghae, South Phyongan, North Phyongan, Jagang and Ryanggang provinces to show the might of the collectives and their optimistic life.

Juche Idea Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- The progressive peoples of the world are highly lauding President Kim Il Sung, founder of the immortal Juche idea which takes the most brilliant position in the history of human thoughts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Juche Philosophy Study Committee of India gave a lecture on the theme of "The August Name of the Great Man Will Shine Forever", in which he said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung had accomplished outstanding feats in the world history of politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His Juche idea is the progressive thought which serves as the guideline in building a new independent world and the immortal guiding idea which represents the future as well as the present day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been brilliantly carried into practice in socialist Korea.  For its truth and vitality, the idea is thus arousing a great sympathy from the broad sections of people around the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His august name is shining in the human history along with the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The minister of State in the Ministry of Water, Lands and Environment of Uganda stated that his Juche idea was the most correct and original one illuminating the road ahead of the struggle of the popular masses for independence and the humankind would be sure to achieve the cause of independence only when it was firmly guided by the idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the French Group for the Study of the Juche Idea stressed: President Kim Il Sung is alive in the minds of the progressives across the world.  He fathered the Juche idea to brightly light the way to be taken by the humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mass media of various countries including the Cambodian newspaper Kmae Amata and the Laotian paper Congtap Pasason Lao introduced the exploits the President had performed for the human history by wisely leading the Korean revolution and the global cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Guinean paper La Nouvelle Tribune wrote: The creation of the Juche idea by President Kim Il Sung was a historic event which brought about an epochal turn in the development of the human thoughts and in the struggle for shaping the destiny of the popular masses.  For its correctness, truth and vitality, the idea has been rapidly spread all over the world, inspiring the people to the struggle for their independence.

Successive S. Korean Fascist Juntas' Human Rights Abuses under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- The National Reconciliation Council issued a white paper Wednesday in which it denounced the successive south Korean fascist juntas for committing human rights abuses against south Koreans, depriving them of their elementary rights and democratic freedom and brutally massacring them after fabricating "pro-communist cases".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The white paper says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They faked up "pro-communist" cases to ruthlessly suppress and kill pro-reunification patriotic figures and innocent people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Syngman Rhee regime was the first to cook up such case in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fascist rulers openly committed terrorism against patriotic figures in a bid to eliminate their political rivals after labeling those patriots "pro-communists" under the backstage manipulation of the U.S. After installing a pro-U.S. separatist regime they enacted the "National Security Law (NSL)", the worst fascist law, in December 1948 in a bid to support the regime by law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the Park Chung Hee military fascist clique seized power through the U.S.-orchestrated "May 16 military coup." It also worked hard to fake up "pro-communist cases" to support the U.S. colonial rule and its dictatorial regime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the miserable end of the "Yusin" fascist dictator, Chun Doo Hwan and Roh Thae Woo fascist juntas wrested power by force of arms to enforce a harsher fascist rule. Then came the Kim Young Sam fascist clique worse than its preceding military dictators as it faked up "pro-communist cases" under the signboard of "civilian government." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean fascist juntas have deprived the south Koreans of their elementary rights and democratic freedom through the most brutal iron fist rule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have even deprived the south Koreans of their right to express their will and give their views on what they have seen and heard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to gratify their political greed, they watched every move of people, men and women, young and old, ranging from politicians, scholars, media persons, businessmen, religionists, youths and students to ordinary citizens and housewives and put them under control. They indiscriminately arrested those incurring their displeasure even a bit and persecuted, tortured and killed them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military gangsters made even a former president aged over 80, "presidential candidate" of an opposition party and their right-hand man targets of execution and terrorism when they considered those figures to be standing in their way of enforcing the fascist rule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean fascist juntas indiscriminately killed innocent people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Every mass-killing committed by the fascist cliques in collusion with outsiders since right after Korea's reunification is recorded as the most shameful hideous crime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is known as "mass killing of civilians" during the Korean war was typical of the massacres that laid bare the fascist cliques' ogrish nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Kwangju Massacre in May 1980 was the most hideous crime against humanity that bore witness to the fascist junta's monstrous mass-killing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fascist laws like NSL which were invoked for human rights abuses in south Korea in the past are still in force there and the descendents and remnants of the fascist cliques are working hard to restore their old regimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Grand National Party of south Korea directly responsible for those human rights abuses has not yet made even a word of apology for the crimes committed by its predecessors. It is instead going so impudent as to talk about "human rights" and "people's interests" in a bid to come to power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP has no right whatsoever to talk about human rights as it has a crime-woven history behind it and it should be, therefore, not allowed to remain in the political arena any longer.

Vice-President of SPA Presidium Meets Mongolian Guest
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a talk with D. Tsogtbaatar, advisor for Foreign Policy to the President of Mongolia, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were an official concerned and the Mongolian ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The advisor said that the friendly and cooperative relations between Mongolia and the DPRK would continue to develop, adding that the Mongolian government would make efforts to further strengthen the relations.

Pyongyang City Meeting Marks Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Work
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- A Pyongyang city meeting was held at Central Youth Hall Wednesday to mark the 35th publication anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's famous work "On the Three Principles of National Reunification".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung in his work clarified the three principles which call for achieving national reunification independently and peacefully on the principle of promoting great national unity free from outside interference under any circumstances and the specific issues arising in achieving the reunification of the country on this basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report was made by Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and vice-chairman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the three principles--independence, peaceful reunification and the great national unity--serve as a programme for reunification common to the nation which the north and the south confirmed at the July 4 Joint Statement and solemnly declared at home and abroad, referring to the tremendous historic significance of the principles in the nation's struggle for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President set forth the three principles of national reunification, the ten-point program for the great unity of the entire nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo, thus providing reasonable and fair guidelines for achieving the country's reunification at the earliest possible date. The exploits the President performed by devoting all his energies and wisdom to the work to bequeath a reunified country to the nation till the last moments of his life will shine for all ages, the reporter added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il formulated the above-said principles, the programme and the proposal for reunification set forth by the President as three charters for national reunification and authored famous works, thus indicating the way of achieving the independent and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter underscored the need for all the Koreans in the north and the south of Korea and abroad to hold fast to the three charters for national reunification and the June 15 joint declaration, its embodiment, and realize the cause of the country's reunification, stressing that the fundamental principles for national reunification and stand on it will remain unchanged no matter how the situation may change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting was attended Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet who is honorary co-chairman of the north side committee for implementing the June 15 joint declaration, Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, Kang Ryon Hak, chairman of the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland, leading officials of political parties, power organs and public organizations, members of the north side committee for implementing the June 15 joint declaration and working people in the city.

Minju Joson denuncia preparacion belica del Sur de Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 2 de mayo (ATCC) -- En estos dias, las autoridades surcoreanas maniobran freneticamente para reforzar y desarrollar los pertrechos belicos sofisticados bajo el activo respaldo e instigacion de Estados Unidos detras de la cortina de dialogo. Esto es un acto criminal peligrosisimo encaminado a obstaculizar la solucion pacifica del problema nuclear de la Peninsula Coreana, exacerbar la tension militar y llevar la situacion a la fase de confrontacion y guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Minju Joson en un comentario individual del dia 2 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Lo mas grave es que el aumento armamentista de las fuerzas belicistas surcoreanas tiene que ver con los ejercicios de guerra de agresion al Norte de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La guerra y la paz son incompatibles. Por lo tanto tal aumento armamentista exacerba la situacion de la Peninsula Coreana, lleva de nuevo las relaciones Norte-Sur a la fase peor, perturba la paz y la seguridad de esta region y el resto de Asia e incrementa la carrera armamentista y el peligro de guerra, lo cual no puede justificarse por nada. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El ejercito y el pueblo de Corea observan con alta vigilancia las temerarias maniobras belicas de agresion al Norte que libran los belicistas de EE.UU. y el Sur de Corea detras de la cortina de dialogo y tomaran medidas decisivas contra ello. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las autoridades surcoreanas deben tener presente de la gravedad de la situacion creada y las consecuencias que emanen de esta y poner inmediatamente fin a su acto provocativo y temerario.

Obreros del Norte y el Sur celebran juntos su dia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Changwon, 1 de mayo (Corresponsal de ATCC) -- En ocasion del Dia Internacional de los Trabajadores, tuvo lugar del 29 de abril al primero de mayo en la ciudad de Changwon de la provincia surcoreana de Kyongsang del Sur la conferencia pro-reunificacion de los obreros del Norte y el Sur para la ejecucion de la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el marco del conclave, se desarrollaron variadas actividades como mitin de unidad, partido futbolistico y encuentro entre los obreros de ambas partes coreanas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La primera actividad tuvo lugar el dia primero en el Complejo Deportivo de Changwon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Participaron en la ocasion los delegados nortenos presididos por Won Hyong Guk, vicepresidente del Comite Central de la Federacion General de los Sindicatos de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por la parte surcoreana, estuvieron presentes los delegados de la "Confederacion de Sindicatos Surcoreanos" encabezados por su presidente Ri Sok Haeng, los representantes de la "Federacion de Sindicatos Surcoreanos" presididos por su titular Ri Yong Duk, los gremiales de organizaciones industriales y regionales en la provincia de Kyongsang del Sur y la ciudad de Changwon y otros surcoreanos de diferentes sectores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Entre los invitados de honor se distinguian el vicepresidente del comite norteno para la Ejecucion de la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio, Ri Chung Bok, el co-delegado de la entidad homologa de la parte Sur, O Jong Ryol, y otras personalidades surcoreanas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sobre todo, se izo la bandera de reunificacion y pronunciaron palabras de felicitacion Ri Chung Bok y O Jong Ryol. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los oradores destacaron la necesidad de unirse en el camino para la reunificacion por encima de las diferencias de idea, criterio politico, sistema y creencia religiosa y de resolver todos los problemas relativos al destino nacional entre los connacionales rechazando cualquier movimiento de las fuerzas foraneas que amenacen la existencia de la nacion coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bien conscientes de su mision asumida ante la epoca, los obreros del Norte y el Sur deben trabajar con sinceridad y patriotismo por la paz del pais, la gran unidad nacional y la reunificacion de la patria, apuntaron los oradores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Les siguieron en acceder al microfono Won Hyong Guk, Ri Yong Duk y Ri Sok Haeng quienes llamaron a lograr la reunificacion independiente y pacifica bajo la bandera de la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio rechazando el dominio e intervencion de las fuerzas foraneas que pretenden frenar la gran marcha de la nacion coreana hacia la reunificacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La declaracion de los obreros del Norte y el Sur aprobada en la ocasion senala que las entidades del movimiento obrero de ambas partes deben materializar consecuentemente la Declaracion Conjunta tomandola por el jalon de la reunificacion independiente y el faro de esperanza y ponerse en la delantera en el cumplimiento de las tres tareas: la preponderancia de la nacion, la defensa de la paz y el logro de la union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Terminado el conclave, transcurrieron la segunda y tercera actividades.
